# scripts/guards/check-no-band-aid-annotations.allowlist
#
# Phase 0a.9 — companion guard to gold-standard-enforcer.
#
# Format (one entry per line):
#   <fingerprint>  # <description> | <annotation>
#
# Separator is "  # " (double-space-hash-space) since fingerprints may contain `#`.
#
# Annotation MUST be one of:
#   | expires: YYYY-MM-DD (cascade: BUG-XXX)
#   | permanent: <reason>
#
# Per Phase 0a.7 expiry retrofit policy + `feedback_no_silent_out_of_scope.md`.
#
# Expiry-policy: per-entry (Phase 0a.7 retrofit)
# Each non-comment line carries an `| expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)`
# OR `| permanent: <reason>` annotation. Entries past their expiry date
# fail the merge gate via `scripts/guards/check-allowlist-expiry.ts`.
# Renewal: when a target close-by date passes, EITHER drain the entry
# (preferred) OR explicitly extend the date with operator authorization.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Categories of legitimate exemptions:
#
# 1. doc-meta-self-referential — the file DOCUMENTS the band-aid rule (e.g.
#    CLAUDE.md describing what a guard's scope IS NOT, fix-build-rules.md
#    section heading naming the rule). The text is a META description of
#    the pattern, not a violation. permanent.
#
# 2. doc-meta-historical — fix-registry rows pinning historical fix patterns
#    where "Out of scope" was the trigger string the fix is anchored on.
#    permanent (the fix stays anchored even though the registry row mentions
#    the pattern).
#
# 3. doc-meta-cascade-row — bugs-remaining.md cascade-drain rows that
#    LITERALLY DESCRIBE the cascade (out of scope of original PR but tracked
#    via cascade BUG-XXX-CASCADE-DRAIN-N row). The cascade BUG row IS the
#    follow-up citation; the row text describing it gets the permanent
#    annotation here. permanent.
#
# 4. doc-meta-template-language — DoD template + verification procedure
#    docs that describe legitimate transient states (e.g. "complete-but-
#    unpushed" is a legitimate intermediate state, not a band-aid).
#    permanent.
#
# 5. doc-meta-plan-scope-section — plan files documenting their own scope
#    boundary in an "Out of scope" section header. Per
#    `feedback_no_silent_out_of_scope.md`, legitimate scope documentation
#    IS allowed; what's prohibited is hiding work behind the fence WITHOUT
#    documenting what the work IS or why it's out. Each plan file's section
#    body enumerates concrete BUG-XXX rows for each out-of-scope item.
#    permanent. Added Phase 0a.9 cycle-2 absorb after extending SCAN_GLOBS
#    to docs/plans/.
#
# Baseline as of Phase 0a.9 cycle-2 absorb — 14 entries total across 5
# categories (10 cycle-1: 4 doc-meta-self-referential + 2 doc-meta-historical
# + 2 doc-meta-cascade-row + 2 doc-meta-template-language; 4 cycle-2:
# doc-meta-plan-scope-section). NEW violations cannot regress without
# explicit allowlist addition with structural rationale.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

docs/quality/bug-447-child-template.md::# Temporarily remove target from allowlist  # bug-447 verification step | permanent: doc-meta-template-language — describes verification procedure step (operator removes from allowlist, runs guard, sees fire, restores). Not a deferral.

