# ─── Plan-file scope-section headings (Phase 0a.9 cycle-2 absorb after extending SCAN_GLOBS to docs/plans/) ───
# Each plan file legitimately documents its own scope boundary in a "Out of scope" section.
# This is doc-meta-plan-scope-section: the section IS the scope-boundary statement for that plan,
# not a band-aid deferral of work. Per `feedback_no_silent_out_of_scope.md`: legitimate scope
# documentation IS allowed; what's prohibited is hiding work behind the fence WITHOUT documenting
# what the work IS or why it's out. Scope-section headings without follow-up BUG citations get
# permanent annotation only if the BODY of the section enumerates concrete BUG-XXX rows for each
# out-of-scope item (which these 4 plans do — verified by reading the section bodies).

